RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 15800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 22, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since December 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOADED SNIPER closed to the lead leaving the seven sixteenths pole and rated the pace, was urged away from the five sixteenths, raced near the rail on the turn and held on under steady handling. PAPA TONY chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the three path, dug in for second mid-stretch and finished well while gaining on the winner. HEY CONGRATS chased inside but steadied at the rail off the inside flank of Loaded Sniper at the seven sixteenths pole, altered course and quickly recovered stride, rounded the turn at the rail and ran evenly down the lane. STRETCH THE TRUTH chased, raced in the five path on the turn but showed little in the lane. GRAND FIBER had brief early lead then gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the turn and flattened the final sixteenth. MOJAC KAT gave chase while saving ground. The Stewards reviewed, then dismissed a claim of foul against the rider of Loaded Sniper, for alleged interference in the vicinity of the seven sixteenths pole, lodged by the rider of Papa Tony.

ENTRY.NAME: Loaded Sniper
ENTRY.OWNER: P and H Stables and C and B Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: up past 7/16,rated pace,urged away 5/16,rail turn,held on driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 13100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCE OF FENTON took the lead approaching the thirteen sixteenths pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, pulled clear of Rocket Dawg nearing the seven sixteenths and steadily drew off to win handily. STAVANGER saved ground, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and settled for second best. SLOE GIN BIZ rounded the first turn in the three path, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and came along for third inside the eighth pole. ROCKET DAWG stalked off the rail, dropped back and gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole but faded in the three path on the far turn. TRANSFER THE FUNDS and EARTHQUAKEDIRECTOR were not factors. SCOOTSCOOT stalked from the four path on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened in the four path on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Stavanger
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 7/16,off rail far turn,settled 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Rocket Dawg
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,dropped back 7/16,faded 3p far turn

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GILDED QUEST veered out leaving the gate then closed to contention and stalked two deep, challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole, took the nod toward the three eighths and dueled from that point, dew clear midway on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane. SOMEBODY LOVES ME was pinched back leaving the gate then saved ground racing well back from early contention, started a bid past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path, dueled for second mid-stretch and finished well. LINDA'S TAJ veered out leaving the gate then rated the pace inside, came under pressure toward the seven sixteenths pole, was met and gave chase toward the three eighths but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and flattened in the stretch. MARQUET CLASSIC settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. RAINBOW RHYTHM stalked through the front stretch but faded on the first turn. TOUGH GAME rounded the opening turn in the four path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but showed little response.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pinched back start,saved ground,bid 7/16,3p far turn,finish well

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOWSAFEAREMYCOLORS became anxious in the gate, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, angled five wide through the turn and dug in under steady encouragement to take over and draw clear later yards. MANAGED MISCHIEF set a pressured pace, rounded the turn near the rail, drifted leaving the turn, dug in under steady encouragement but was caught in later yards. GREAT DEVOTION chased through the backstretch, raced close at the rail on the turn and ran evenly to late stretch before flattening stride. QUEEN OF KANTHAROS pressured the pace through the backstretch, raced close off the rail on the turn, was carried out leaving the turn and ran evenly to late stretch before flattening. TAKE CHARGE LISA chased, raced close four wide on the turn then flattened mid-stretch. AMERICAN BOUND became anxious in the gate then gave chase, raced in the four path on the turn but showed little in the lane. SHAKE IT GIRL became a bit edgy in the gate and saved ground. FLAT OUT COOL was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY SLICK NICK settled back off the rail on the first turn, eased out into the backstretch and picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, improved in the four path of the far turn, took over approaching the head of the lane, drew clear and held well under steady handling. NET WORTH raced well off the pace in the four path the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, improved in the six path of the far turn then dueled through the stretch for second. MR MAJESTIC saved ground, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in tight at the rail toward the head of the lane and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. MIMS SECOND CHANCE had a brief early lead then stalked, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole, raced close in the three path of the far turn but flattened inside the eighth pole. GAMMA SQUEEZE saved ground racing well back on the opening turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced blocked at the rail approaching the head of the lane but finished evenly. A THOUSAND IDOLS bobbled a stride from the gate and settled in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths, rounded the far turn in the three path and weakened in the lane. DANNY'S WINKSTER tapered in and took the lead toward the three quarter pole and rated the pace, came under pressure past the three eighths, was met at the rail nearing the eighth pole and weakened in the lane. SHAMELESS APPEAL stalked off the rail, gave chase into the backstretch but weakened into the far turn. SMOKIN SMITTY showed little response.

ENTRY.NAME: My Slick Nick
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,4p far turn,up near 1/8,drving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Races Whe re Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINDSOR'S TRACKER was crowded leaving the gate and raced off the rail on the first turn, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn and dug in determinedly to eke out the nod over the game stretch effort of ORANGEBURG, who came outward leaving the gate then stalked off the rail, challenged approaching the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms from that point, took the nod toward the five sixteenths, contested the advantage at the rail on the far turn and dug in gamely through the lane before relenting the final yards. AIR MEDAL was crowded leaving the gate then saved ground, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and came along for third the final yards. SIENTE EL AMOR closed to the lead while tapering inward and rated the pace, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms, but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and flattened mid-stretch. MR CHANCE ROMANCE came in after the start, rounded the first turn about the three path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded in the three path on the far turn. CHASE LIL ME was crowded leaving the gate then saved ground well back, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn, left the turn outside and passed some rivals. GET OFF MY CLOUD showed little response through the backstretch. BLUE N GOLD rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. The Stewards reviewed, then dismissed a claim of foul against the rider of Air Medal for alleged interference leaving the gate, lodged by the rider of Chase Lil Me.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 22 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowa nces)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER JORDAN chased inside and took the lead at the rail midway on the turn, dug in under steady stretch handling and held on. ALLEN CAN DO IT chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the four and five paths, dueled for second mid-stretch and was gaining on the winner. FIBER STRONG gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn and dug in to take third later yards. ATLANTIC VAQUERO chased through the backstretch, raced in the three path on the turn, drifted toward the head of the lane then flattened later yards. JEFFERSON NATIVE became a little unsettled in the gate and was unprepared for the break, lacked a clear early path but was eased outward and gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the turn about the five path and ran evenly in the lane. FIFTY FIFTY took a quick lead and set the early pace while tapering in, was met while two deep midway on the turn, dropped back toward the head of the lane and weakened leaving the eighth pole. BODYSLAM was never a factor. ALWAYS HOPEFUL gave chase then faded at the rail on the turn. HELL'S KITTEN was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Fiber Strong
ENTRY.OWNER: Pascal Lawrence J and Harding Sr Philip Arthur

ENTRY.NAME: Jefferson Native
ENTRY.COMMENT: unprepared break,lacked early room,chased 3/8,5p turn,evenly lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIS ROYAL G stalked from the three and four paths the first turn, bid leaving the three eighths pole and raced close off the rail on the far turn, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and inched clear under the wire. NIGHT TRAIN WAYNE took the lead leaving the three quarter pole and rated the pace, came under pressure toward the quarter pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn but was met mid-stretch and relented later yards. MISS YOU AJAX stalked toward the inside on the opening turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then dueled through the stretch for third. EISELE steadied in tight at the rail midway on the first turn and settled off the pace, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. ROCK FILE saved ground well off the pace, bid leaving the five sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and passed rivals. BOP MARLEY rounded the first turn about the five path, entered the backstretch outside and picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn and showed little in the lane. BOSEY raced in the four path on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path and weakened in the lane. EL TOLU saved ground, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but flattened at the rail on the far turn. A FAREWELL YODEL was never a factor. BRIGHT DAWN rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened in the four path on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: His Royal G
ENTRY.OWNER: Pepe Stable and J L M Jacona Stable
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3& 4p,bid 3/8,off rail far turn,up 1/16,inched clear wire
